  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Critical support to ensure food security and agriculture-based subsistence livelihoods of drought affected population in Balochistan and Sindh provinces of Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide emergency agriculture and livestock assistance to the drought-affected agro-pastoralist communities in the targeted districts of Balochistan and Sindh provinces. FAO will use CERF to provide animal fodder and veterinary support to 30,000 livestock owning families, crop seeds to 3,000 families, homestead gardening packages to 2,500 female-headed households, as well as rehabilitation of damaged irrigation systems through a cash-for-work scheme. An estimated 223,200 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within six months.</narrative>
  </description>
